{"insight":"A word carries the life that trained it","publicTitle":"No Word Travels Alone","plainSummary":"A sacred word can heal or harm depending on the practice, correction, test, and wound that meet it.","atAGlance":"A sacred word arrives with more than meaning. It brings the way it was practiced, the people who corrected it, and the tests that kept it honest. In a wounded life, the same word can bend toward fear, shame, hiding, or self-erasure. A teaching should name both its old discipline and its likely misuse today.","keyPoints":["Meaning depends on the practice that shaped the word.","Pain can turn a good word into permission to disappear.","Test whether the word brings clearer care or deeper escape."],"match":["no word travels alone"],"tags":["language","practice","care"]}
